{"TopicId":168030,"ForumId":55,"TopicTitle":"Mobile Version of KSP","CreatedByName":"kris10127","CreatedById":183154,"CreatedDateTime":"2017-11-28T23:03:39Z","PageNum":7,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jo\u00E3o722772","CreatedById":220236,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-18T20:24:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Catto","CreatedById":137773,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-19T04:19:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224103992\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221647635086\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022220236\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jo\u00E3o722772\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Jo\u00E3o722772 said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHello\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"darthgently","CreatedById":204885,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-03-20T05:12:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223282338\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221517422480\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022184951\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022ChairmanJones\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/31/2018 at 1:14 PM, ChairmanJones said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUnity 5 can build for iOS and Android, it\u0027s technically feasible and several games use the Unity engine on mobile fairly well. Moving to a touch interface is the challenge.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI could see a simplified version working fine on higher powered phones.\u00A0 But I think that \u0022welding\u0022 of multiple parts into a single part to keep part count down and a lower ceiling on part counts for craft.\u00A0 If graphics aspects that affect performance were dialed down, like terrain detail, mesh densities, texture resolution, maybe even a reduced palette, simplified visual effects, etc, it is probably doable in a playable way.\u00A0 But it wouldn\u0027t be the same.\u00A0 It would be more like Doom before GPUs.\u00A0 More like a cross between Simple Rockets and KSP.\u00A0 Which could be worth buying depending\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"tater","CreatedById":119411,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T17:31:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOn the plus side is that iOS and MacOS are now compatible. So iOS gets iPad, iPhones, and Macs all into the bargain.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T17:47:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223915867\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221611805233\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002264714\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gargamel\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 1/28/2021 at 3:40 AM, Gargamel said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP runs acceptably well on very old hardware\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing liberal with the meaning of acceptably, yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T18:33:44Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224123402\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651081651\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n41 minutes ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBeing liberal with the meaning of acceptably, yes.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP 1.4.3 runs absolutely fine on 2012 hardware (if you max out the memory, it\u0027s nearly perfect).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe worst bottleneck since KSP 1.8.0 are the crappy Unity handling of threads (busy waits everywhere - also known as spin-locks) and the Parts revamp that nearly doubled\u00A0 the RAM and VRAM consuption without functional gains (and with the UI bug applying mipmaps on GUI glyphs, lowering the texture quality renders the UI nearly unusable).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"BekfastDerp13","CreatedById":214450,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T19:07:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomeone probably suggested this already, but just get Simplerockets. I know it\u0027s not the same but it\u0027s the next best alternative.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Bej Kerman","CreatedById":182413,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T19:11:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224123417\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651084424\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n37 minutes ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nParts revamp\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t get me started. The immense effort Squad put into \u0022refining\u0022 0.01% of the parts overall made the game 25% worse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-27T19:25:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224123433\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651086703\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n8 hours ago, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t get me started. The immense effort Squad put into \u0022refining\u0022 0.01% of the parts overall made the game 25% worse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe refining was OK IMHO.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe never fixed bugs on the codebase are the culprits.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHad the Texture Quality be correctly implemented, you could just reduce the Texture Quality and keep playing normally.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nProof of Concept: make a full backup of the whole KSP 1.12.3 installment and on the copy, run ImageMagick resizing all DDS files with more than 64x64 pixels to 75% or even 50% and then go for a test drive on your old rig.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you trimm the resizing to use the better algorithm for each image (some complex textures look bad on the fastest ones), you will get a significantly enhancement in the performance without too much impact (if ever, if you are really on a Potato like me) on the Visuals.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe ground texturing is also a CPU hog nowadays -by the way. I don\u0027t think the extra burden on my rig worths the visual enhancements,\u00A0 but that thing is locked on high qualify no matter the setting I use.\u00A0 \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:(\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_sad.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:(\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EApparently the increased size of the PQS cache on 1.4.4 screwed me up royally on my old MacCrap. I would had made good use of an option to set the size of the PQS cache to the one used by 1.4.3.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E--- POST EDIT ---\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EIn a nutshell, right now I have a computer with twice the cores, twice the RAM e 3 times more VRAM and yet KSP 1.12.x performs 4 times worst then KSP 1.4.3 running on my original machine.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003EI used to get 60 FPS on small crafts on the older rig.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ENow I get 15 to 20 tops on the Space Center. Loading a simple craft into flight drops the FPS to 13 or 14 - with blurry graphics, because I had to lower the texture quality and it screws up the User Interface.\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222022-04-28T04:15:54Z\u0022 title=\u002204/28/2022 04:15  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00222 yr\u0022\u003EApril 28, 2022\u003C/time\u003E by Lisias\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003EHate autocompletes\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-29T04:59:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224123433\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651086703\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022182413\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Bej Kerman\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 4/27/2022 at 4:11 PM, Bej Kerman said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDon\u0027t get me started. The immense effort Squad put into \u0022refining\u0022 0.01% of the parts overall made the game 25% worse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDude, your guesses were interestingly accurate!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGive a peek on the numbers \u00A0of this post:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed815149240\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/207971-how-to-play-ksp-with-unity-2019-on-old-potatoes-part-ii/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:191px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerodynamic Kerbal","CreatedById":211338,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-29T07:35:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP on mobile will be like GTA V on a Nokia 3310!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if there are less parts, worse graphics, it might work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-29T19:46:43Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124135\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651217715\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aerodynamic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n12 hours ago, Aerodynamic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP on mobile will be like GTA V on a Nokia 3310!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut if there are less parts, worse graphics, it might work.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like KSP 1.2.2 would do fine on it, I think. Once someone cooks a viable UI for the thing - mouse style UI will not cut it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerodynamic Kerbal","CreatedById":211338,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T06:40:13Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124422\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651261603\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n10 hours ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSomething like KSP 1.2.2 would do fine on it, I think. Once someone cooks a viable UI for the thing - mouse style UI will not cut it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried playing with my PS4 controller on my phone. It worked out with Bluetooth. So I guess the controls could not oppose a problem - just get a cheap controller and you\u0027re done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T06:47:24Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124580\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651300813\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022211338\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Aerodynamic Kerbal\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 minutes ago, Aerodynamic Kerbal said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ve tried playing with my PS4 controller on my phone. It worked out with Bluetooth. So I guess the controls could not oppose a problem - just get a cheap controller and you\u0027re done.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, indeed, Bluetooth keyboards and mice can also be connected to Android devices. That solves matters for the player, but it would be hard for a company to sell something to mobile users that requires an additional hardware purchase. There would have to be a working touch-screen interface as well, or hardware would have to be bundled with the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aerodynamic Kerbal","CreatedById":211338,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T06:51:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124582\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651301244\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, indeed, Bluetooth keyboards and mice can also be connected to Android devices. That solves matters for the player, but it would be hard for a company to sell something to mobile users that requires an additional hardware purchase. There would have to be a working touch-screen interface as well, or hardware would have to be bundled with the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThere should, but if you happen to have a controller or Bluetooth keyboard and mouse, problem solved!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Lisias","CreatedById":187168,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T08:22:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124582\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651301244\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002262955\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Deddly\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Deddly said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnd, indeed, Bluetooth keyboards and mice can also be connected to Android devices. That solves matters for the player, but it would be hard for a company to sell something to mobile users that requires an additional hardware purchase. There would have to be a working touch-screen interface as well, or hardware would have to be bundled with the game.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI would \u0022love\u0022 to see someone pulling a IR keyboard and a Finger mouse somewhere on the wild, like a bus or an airplane! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler\u0022 data-ipsspoiler=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_header\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003ESpoiler\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsSpoiler_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022ProjectionKeyboard_2.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022162.00\u0022 height=\u0022900\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/b/b4/ProjectionKeyboard_2.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u002241IMIi-mI\u002BL._AC_SL1005_.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002260.92\u0022 height=\u0022594\u0022 width=\u0022975\u0022 src=\u0022https://m.media-amazon.com/images/I/41IMIi-mI\u002BL._AC_SL1005_.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Deddly","CreatedById":62955,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-04-30T09:20:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224124608\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022168030\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221651306972\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022187168\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Lisias\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n56 minutes ago, Lisias said:\n\u003C